<title>UK: Ford says Halewood job losses to be 980.</title>
<headline>Ford says Halewood job losses to be 980.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>American car giant Ford Motor Co confirmed on Friday that under a deal with unions it had agreed to reduce redundancies at its Halewood plant in north east England to 980 employees from the originally planned 1,300.</p>
<p>Jack Nasser, head of Ford's European division, told a news conference that the company had also committed itself to additional investment in Britain as part of the agreement.</p>
